## FLOW 10 — CI/CD & Deployment Pipeline

```
Developer Machine        GitHub                 GitHub Actions              Railway
  │                         │                       │                          │
  ├─git push origin staged──►│                       │                          │
  │                         ├─trigger workflow .yml──►│                         │
  │                         │                       ├─./mvnw verify             │
  │                         │                       │  (compile + test + jacooc)│
  │                         │                       ├─docker build              │
  │                         │                       │  (multi-stage Dockerfile) │
  │                         │                       ├─docker push registry──────►│
  │                         │                       │                          ├─pull new image
  │                         │                       │                          ├─start container
  │                         │                       │                          ├─poll /health/readiness
  │                         │                       │                          │  (InventoryWarmupHealthIndicator)
  │                         │                       │                          ├─warm-up @PostConstruct
  │                         │                       │                          │  (Redis inventory load)
  │                         │                       │                          ├─readiness=UP
  │                         │                       │                          ├─route traffic to new instance
  │                         │                       │                          ├─drain old instance
```

---

## CROSS-CUTTING CONCERNS — Applied to Every Flow

```
EVERY HTTP REQUEST:
  │
  ├─[1] CorrelationIdFilter (Order=1, before all else)
  │      Extract X-Correlation-ID header (or generate UUID)
  │      MDC.put("correlationId", id)
  │      response.setHeader(X-Correlation-ID, id) ← echoed back to client
  │
  ├─[2] JwtFilter
  │      Extract "Authorization: Bearer {token}"
  │      JwtService.validateToken() → userId, role, expiry
  │      SecurityContextHolder.setAuthentication(...)
  │
  ├─[3] SecurityConfig authorization rules
  │      /api/auth/** → permitAll()
  │      /api/webhooks/** → no JWT (Stripe signature = auth)
  │      everything else → authenticated()
  │
  ├─[4] Controller method
  │      @PreAuthorize("hasRole('ORGANIZER')") where applicable
  │      @Valid on request body DTO → 400 if invalid
  │
  ├─[5] Service method (inside @Transactional boundary)
  │      Business logic
  │      DB reads/writes via HikariCP → PostgreSQL
  │      Redis operations via RedisTemplate
  │      RabbitMQ publishes via RabbitTemplate
  │           └─ message.setHeader(X-Correlation-ID, MDC.get("correlationId"))
  │
  ├─[6] Response
  │      API response wrapped in ApiResponse<T>
  │      X-Correlation-ID header echoed
  │
  └─[7] CorrelationIdFilter finally block
         MDC.remove("correlationId") ← ALWAYS cleaned up

EVERY RABBITMQ CONSUMER:
  ├─Extract X-Correlation-ID from message headers
  ├─MDC.put("correlationId", id)
  ├─process message
  └─MDC.remove("correlationId") in finally block
```

